title: Print, 1635
medium: Etching on off white laid paper
inscribed: Inscribed in pen and brown ink, upper center margin: 44; upper right margin: 48. Inscribed in graphite lower left margin: D1085; lower center margin: 1 A A (each underlined). Inscribed on plate, lower left: ABosse in. et fe.; lower left border: le Blond excud. Avec Privilege du Roy.
creditline: Gift of Mrs. Henry B. du Pont
description: Scene of the interior of a house. At left a group of women are making fritters over an open fire. At center a table is being set. At right beyond a bed frame, a woman stands before a mirror. Image enclosed in engraved frame

tombstone.epitaph:
Print, 1635.
1635. Etching on off white laid paper. Gift of Mrs. Henry B. du Pont. 1951-126-11.
